<section class="section" id="our-process">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">How It Works</div>
    <h2 class="section-heading">A Typical Engagement, Week by Week</h2>
    <div class="section-body">
      <p>Every project is different, but the structure is proven. We do the heavy lifting. You keep running your operation.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="process-timeline">
      <div class="process-week">
        <div class="process-dot">P</div>
        <div class="process-week-label">Pre-Project</div>
        <h3>Background Data Collection</h3>
        <p>Before anyone sets foot on site, we collect historical operating data, current schedule descriptions for every department, planned work levels, and cost information. We arrive prepared.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-week">
        <div class="process-dot">1</div>
        <div class="process-week-label">Week 1 · On-Site</div>
        <h3>Discovery &amp; Kickoff</h3>
        <p>Project kickoff with leadership and supervisors. Meetings with each work area to understand their role, current schedule, requirements, and issues. Individual sessions with the controller, HR, and safety. This week is about listening.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-week">
        <div class="process-dot">2</div>
        <div class="process-week-label">Week 2 · Off-Site</div>
        <h3>Business Analysis</h3>
        <p>Analyze everything collected in Week 1. Build the business case. Develop cost, benefit, and risk analysis. Prepare preliminary findings and schedule modeling.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-week">
        <div class="process-dot">3</div>
        <div class="process-week-label">Week 3 · On-Site</div>
        <h3>Analysis Review &amp; Survey Prep</h3>
        <p>Review business analysis with leadership. Finalize the workforce survey instrument based on what we learned about your specific operation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-week">
        <div class="process-dot">4</div>
        <div class="process-week-label">Week 4 · On-Site</div>
        <h3>Employee Orientation &amp; Survey</h3>
        <p>Employee orientation and survey meetings. Every affected employee participates. Consultants available for individual questions. This is where workforce involvement begins in earnest.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-week">
        <div class="process-dot">5</div>
        <div class="process-week-label">Week 5 · Off-Site</div>
        <h3>Survey Processing &amp; Report</h3>
        <p>Process survey results. Tabulate by overall results and by demographic groups — departments, shifts, family care responsibilities. Build the comparison report with normative benchmarks.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-week">
        <div class="process-dot">6</div>
        <div class="process-week-label">Week 6 · On-Site</div>
        <h3>Options Development</h3>
        <p>Present survey results to management. Develop schedule options and pay policies based on what the survey revealed. Begin implementation documentation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-week">
        <div class="process-dot">7</div>
        <div class="process-week-label">Week 7 · On-Site</div>
        <h3>Employee Choice &amp; Implementation</h3>
        <p>Present options to all affected personnel. Distribute implementation documentation. Collect schedule preference forms. The workforce chooses — and the schedule they pick becomes their schedule.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-week">
        <div class="process-dot">✓</div>
        <div class="process-week-label">Follow-Up</div>
        <h3>Post-Implementation Review</h3>
        <p>Conduct a follow-up survey after implementation. Measure satisfaction, identify any issues, and make adjustments. We don't disappear after Week 7.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

